  "doc_id": "14186",
  "text": "The mechanisms contributing to reduction of hepatic fibrosis by the combination of empagliflozin and linagliptin remain unclear. One possible explanation for the anti-fibrotic effect of this combination therapy is that linagliptin prevents the infiltration of macrophages (F4/80 positive cells) into lobular lesions, while empagliflozin inhibits the hepatic expression of proinflammatory cytokines such as IL-6, TNF-α, and MCP-1, which are regarded as hallmarks of NASH [CITATION_1] . Thus, inhibition of inflammation in the liver may contribute to inhibition of hepatic fibrosis in NASH mice treated with the combination of empagliflozin and linagliptin.",
